original: Falck, Nils Christer Georg August, fd. rådman. Långedrag, f. 3/5/74 i Malmö av fördeln:läk. Johan August F. o. Charlotte Åberg. G. 05 m. Signe Westrup. B’arn: Yngve f. 06, Bengt 08, Cecilia 11, Rigmor 17, Barbro 18. — Mog:ex. i Malmö 91, jur. fil. ex. i Lund 93, hovr :ex. 01. E. o. not. i hovr. över Skåne o. Blek. 0’1, tingstjg. 03-04, e. not. i Gbgs rådhusr. 05, stadsnot. 11, rådm. 25. RNO, RVO.
translated: Falck, Nils Christer Georg August, former magistrate. Långedrag, born May 3rd, 1874 in Malmö, son of physician Johan August F. and Charlotte Åberg. Married in 1905 to Signe Westrup. Children: Yngve born in 1906, Bengt 1908, Cecilia 1911, Rigmor 1917, Barbro 1918. Completed medical examination in Malmö in 1891, degree in law and philosophy in Lund in 1893, and judicial examination in 1901. Acted as assistant notary in the Court of Appeals for Skåne and Blekinge in 1901, district court clerk from 1903-1904, notary in the Gothenburg City Council in 1905, city notary in 1911, magistrate in 1925. Received RNO (Order of the Sword) and RVO (Order of Vasa).
